# Sync with git before working on the app

This repo has multiple contributors and an auto-updater that commits live match
scores. Working on a stale local copy means reviewing the wrong tournament state
and risking an ugly merge later. So **before starting any review or feature work**:

1. `git status` — see what's uncommitted locally.
2. `git fetch` — then compare against the remote (`git log --oneline HEAD..origin/master`
   and `git rev-list --count HEAD..origin/master`).
3. Integrate the latest: commit (or stash) local work, then `git merge origin/master`.
   Resolve any conflicts before continuing.
4. After the merge, run `npx vitest run` and `npm run build` to confirm nothing broke.
5. Only then start the review/work, so it's against the current tournament data.

When pushing your own work back, merge remote first and re-run tests/build to make
sure the merge didn't break anything existing. Never force-push to `master`.

## PowerShell notes (this is a Windows + PowerShell shell)

- Chain commands with `;`, not `&&`.
- Don't use `@{u}` / `@{upstream}` — PowerShell parses `@{...}` as a hashtable.
  Use the explicit ref instead, e.g. `origin/master`.
